# Solicitation Summary: FA940126Q0002 – Aircrew Facility Linens

---

## Project Overview
- **Solicitation Title:** Aircrew Facility Linens
- **Solicitation Number:** FA940126Q0002
- **Agency:** Department of the Air Force, 377th Air Base Wing (AFGSC), Kirtland AFB Contracting Division
- **Location:** Building 917, Kirtland Air Force Base, Albuquerque, NM 87117-0001
- **Type & Set Aside:** 100% SDVOSB (Service Disabled Veteran Owned Small Business) set aside, NAICS 812320 ($8M size standard)
- **Description:** Contractor to provide comprehensive linen laundering and dry cleaning for aircrew facility at KAFB. Services must meet industry, federal, state, local, and health/safety standards; project is mission essential; contractor may be required to perform during crisis conditions.

---

## Key Dates
- **Solicitation Posted:** 7 November 2025
- **Questions Due:** 30 October 2025, 5:00 PM (MDT/MST)
- **Quote Submission Deadline:** 14 November 2025, 4:00 PM (MDT/MST)
- **Quote Validity:** 90 days
- **Anticipated Start:** 1 December 2025

### Period of Performance
- **Base Year:** 1 Dec 2025 – 30 Nov 2026 (up to 40,000 lbs)
- **Option Years I-IV:** Each subsequent 12 months through 30 Nov 2030 (each 40,000 lbs/yr)
- **6-Month Extension Possible**

---

## Key Contacts
- **Contract Specialist:** Andrew Wiseman – andrew.wiseman.2@us.af.mil
- **Contracting Officer:** Dakota Powell – dakota.powell@us.af.mil
- **COR/Performance POC:** Latesha Davis – latesha.davis@us.af.mil, 505-846-6298

---

## Submission Requirements
- **Submission Format:** Email only; .pdf, .doc, or .xls formats (max 30MB); no .zip files.
- **Quote Content:** Max 5-6 page technical plan, strong focus on adherence to PWS. No marketing/extraneous info. Any exceptions to terms must be explicitly identified and justified.
- **Evaluation:**
    - Agreement with solicitation terms
    - Acceptable technical plan (see PWS, esp. Section 4.5)
    - Fair/reasonable pricing; evaluation proceeds by ranking prices, lowest four reviewed for technical acceptability first, then fifth, etc. as needed.
    - All options included in evaluated price.

---

## Documents Included
1. **Attachment 1:** Performance Work Statement (PWS) – detailed requirements and quality standards
2. **Attachment 2:** Wage Determination 2015-5443 Rev. 26 (dated 8 July 2025)
3. **Attachment 3:** SF1449 Solicitation (provisions, clauses)
4. **Annex 1:** Pricing Schedule
5. **Reference Photos:** Building 917

---

## Insurance & Compliance Requirements
- **Insurance:** Not individually specified; contractor must comply with all local, state, federal, and industry regulations and standards. (Refer to PWS & solicitation clauses for any additional required coverage).
- **Labor:** Must comply with Service Contract Labor Standards (see Wage Determination attachment).
- **Safety/Local Restrictions:** All work must comply with AFOSH and base health/safety protocols. No government furnished equipment/utilities; contractor responsible for transportation, pickup, delivery, and all necessary tools/supplies.

---

## Additional Restrictions & Info
- **No Incumbent:** This is a new requirement with no prior contractor.
- **NMGRT:** New Mexico Gross Receipts Tax may apply.
- **FOB Point:** Destination 
- **Invoicing:** Monthly; verified by COR; reporting of items/lbs processed and lost items required.
- **Facility:** No emergency generator in Building 917; recent upgrades to plumbing, HVAC, etc.
- **Cancellation/Funding:** Award subject to funds availability; may be canceled at any time before award if funds become unavailable.

